  <bioghist audience="internal" id="aspace_aca90fb082ab5b6e59ba8352f6a4343d">
    <head>Biographical / Historical</head>
<p>George Alan Fisher, born January 6, 1938, in Los Angeles, worked for a number of airlines in the cargo traffic section, export and import, first in California, then from ca. 1965-1967 in Copenhagen for a Scandinavian airline, SAS, and then for 23 years at JFK airport in New York City for Japan Airlines. He retired in June 1990. Under the name Ed Drucker, he ran Elysian Fields, Booksellers, from its opening in 1972 until his death. Elysian Fields specialized in out of print gay, lesbian, and bisexual fiction and non-fiction with some general sexuality books as well. Fisher traveled worldwide. He died on October 3, 1990.</p>  </bioghist>
